    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ranged Tactics Toolbox pg. 0</em>, <em>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 142</em>, <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 17</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 50 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 8 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d8 (small), 1d10 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> 19-20/x2; <strong>Range</strong> 120 ft.; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> -</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Ranged; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Simple</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Crossbows</p><h3>Description</h3><p>You draw a heavy crossbow back by turning a small winch. Loading a heavy crossbow is a full-round action that provokes attacks of opportunity. A heavy crossbow fires crossbow bolts.</p><p>Normally, operating a heavy crossbow requires two hands. However, you can shoot, but not load, a heavy crossbow with one hand at a -4 penalty on attack rolls. You can shoot a heavy crossbow with each hand, but you take a penalty on attack rolls as if attacking with two one-handed weapons. This penalty is cumulative with the penalty for one-handed firing.</p>"
